ining beaten egg yolk."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"Place lemon juice, sugar, butter and lemon zest in mixing bowl then heat <b>5 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Without measuring cup, mix <b>2 min\/80°C\/speed 3<b> while adding eggs, followed by egg yolks, one at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid. Insert measuring cup then continue heating <b>4 min\/80°C\/speed 3<b> until mixture thickens like lemon curd. Pour into prepared pastry shell. Set aside in fridge to chill for at least 2 hours."},{"content":"Remove from tin, then dust with icing sugar and serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a bruléed finish, before serving, place chilled tart dusted with icing sugar under a very hot grill for up to a minute until small brown spots appear on surface (do not let pastry burn). Chill before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","4h 30m","8 slices"]}